      <section class="endorsement-howto shelf-howto panel">
        <h2>About This Section</h2>
        <p>
          This shelf gathers essays, reflections, and foundational documents that consider how
          economic life is shaped not only by markets and incentives, but by moral obligation,
          institutional power, and the terms by which people live together.
        </p>
        <p>
          A central concern here is scale: what happens when systems become large enough that
          responsibility is dispersed, authority is obscured, and harm can be inflicted without
          direct intent and yet with very real consequence. These works ask how legitimacy is
          sustained or lost under such conditions, and what covenantal language might recover
          that purely procedural language often cannot.
        </p>
